    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-10T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/195: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. The American Embassy at Vichy (Paris) has been informed by Wellington Koo
                    that “according to Chungking the Soviet Union has waived claim to the <hi
                        rend="italic">Selenga</hi> cargo” and reports further that Koo “understood
                    that Moscow would instruct the Soviet Chargé at Vichy accordingly”. French
                    officials have advised the American Embassy that if this is the situation, the
                    French Government will give orders for the immediate release of the ores in
                    question.</p>
                <p>The Department has not yet been informed however that the Soviet Government has
                    taken any action on the matter and believes it possible that Wellington Koo was
                    misinformed or misunderstood his instructions. Your 382, August 6, 5 p.m.,<note
                        n="35" xml:id="d767fn35">Quoted in telegram No. 235, August 6, 8 p.m., <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> does not indicate that the matter has
                    been cleared with the Moscow Government by the Chungking Government. Please
                    check with the Chinese authorities, report to the Department, and secure if
                    desirable clarifying instructions to Wellington Koo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
